<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
Add a bibliography at the end of your essay citing all relevant sources used in your research, regardless of whether they are explicitly mentioned in your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br><br>
When there is no publication or modified date, place an access date before the URL e.g. &#8216;&hellip;Accessed June 30, 2015. http.//wwwjnxhr.org&hellip;&#8217;. An access date may also be used if instructed by your tutor or lecturer in cases where websites are subject to change.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author 1 (surname, given name), and Author 2 (name in normal order). &#34;Title of Article.&#34; <em>Journal Title</em> volume, no. issue (year): pages. Web address.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author 1 (surname, given name), and Author 2 (name in normal order)">Upton, Aroha, and Bridget Brown</span>. 
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of Article">Dining Out: A History of Restaurant Eating in New Zealand</span>.&#34; 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Journal Title">Journal of New Zealand Historical Research</span></em> 
	<span class="hover" title="volume">10</span>, 
	no. <span class="hover" title="issue">2</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="year">2056</span>): 
	<span class="hover" title="pages">154&#45;65</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Web address">http://www.jnzhr.org.nz/UB1002</span>.
</blockquote>
